{"id":82008,"title":"The Italian perspective on fluoride intake in children and adolescents.","abstract":"This paper represents the outcome of the meetings of the Committee composed by Pedodontists (SIOI - Italian Society of Paediatric Dentistry) and Paediatricians (FIMP - Italian Association of Paediatricians) with the aim to share an evidence- based common approach in caries prevention during childhood and adolescence. The most important topic was an update on fluoride administration methods in order to minimise the risk of fluorosis and maximise its caries-preventive effect.The conclusions of this work are exposed in a synoptic table.","date":"2014-04-21","categories":"Stomatognathic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24745594","annotations":[{"name":"Dentistry","weight":0.697137,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dentistry"},{"name":"Preventive medicine","weight":0.475564,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preventive_medicine"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.275305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"Italy","weight":0.209872,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy"},{"name":"Evidence-based medicine","weight":0.166395,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidence-based_medicine"},{"name":"Adolescence","weight":0.147927,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolescence"},{"name":"Childhood","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Childhood"},{"name":"Fluoride","weight":0.0453442,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluoride"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk"},{"name":"Paper","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paper"},{"name":"Evidence","weight":0.0332387,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidence"},{"name":"Dental fluorosis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipe